- id: wrangler-init
  subject: Initialize Wrangler Worker project
  status: pending
  description: Create wrangler.toml, package.json, src/index.ts for CF Worker
  effort: small
  category: infra
  blocking: [cors-middleware, auth-middleware, router, ws-proxy]
  blockedBy: []
  acceptance:
    - wrangler.toml present with correct name/main/compatibility_date
    - package.json has wrangler devDep
    - src/index.ts exports fetch handler

- id: auth-middleware
  subject: Implement bearer token auth gate
  status: pending
  description: All requests must carry Authorization header with matching token. Token stored in Worker secret (env var). 401 on missing/invalid. OPTIONS preflight bypasses auth.
  effort: small
  category: feature
  blocking: [router]
  blockedBy: [wrangler-init]
  acceptance:
    - Missing token returns 401
    - Wrong token returns 401
    - Correct token passes through
    - OPTIONS bypasses auth check

- id: cors-middleware
  subject: Implement CORS header injection
  status: pending
  description: Every response gets CORS headers. Configurable allowed origins via env. OPTIONS preflight returns 204 with full CORS headers immediately.
  effort: small
  category: feature
  blocking: [router]
  blockedBy: [wrangler-init]
  acceptance:
    - OPTIONS returns 204 with Access-Control-Allow-* headers
    - All proxied responses include CORS headers
    - Origin configurable via ALLOWED_ORIGINS env var

- id: router
  subject: Implement traffic router / proxy
  status: pending
  description: Route table maps path prefixes to upstream Worker URLs or origins. HTTP and WebSocket traffic both handled. Route table defined via ROUTES env var (JSON). Unknown routes return 404.
  effort: medium
  category: feature
  blocking: [ws-proxy]
  blockedBy: [auth-middleware, cors-middleware]
  acceptance:
    - HTTP requests forwarded to correct upstream preserving method/headers/body
    - WebSocket upgrade requests tunneled via fetch with Upgrade header
    - Unknown path returns 404 JSON
    - Route table hot-swappable via env var

- id: ws-proxy
  subject: Implement WebSocket proxying
  status: pending
  description: Detect Upgrade: websocket header. Use CF WebSocket pair trick to tunnel WS through Worker to upstream. Bidirectional message forwarding.
  effort: medium
  category: feature
  blocking: []
  blockedBy: [router]
  acceptance:
    - WS upgrade forwarded to upstream
    - Messages flow both directions
    - Close frames propagated

- id: debug-endpoint
  subject: Add /debug/routes observability endpoint
  status: pending
  description: GET /debug/routes returns current route table, auth status (token present yes/no), CF metadata. Auth-gated.
  effort: small
  category: infra
  blocking: []
  blockedBy: [router]
  acceptance:
    - Returns JSON with routes, worker name, CF colo
    - Requires valid bearer token
